body:
Wrecked

Fandom: BTS

Pairing:  Namjin, Jikook, Vmin

Status:  One shot

Words:  2703

Beta:  Tanya

Summary:  Jungkook discovers the truth and is devastated.

Snippet:

It had been difficult to seduce Taehyung, even though they had been flirting with each other since the day they met.  Jimin smiles because he had succeeded in awaking Taehyung’s sleeping sexuality…and it electrified him.  Sometimes when Taehyung is fucking him Jimin feels like he is escaping from the world.

Jimin is busy contemplating all the things he wants the other man to do to him once they get home when he feels Taehyung pull away.

Suddenly Jimin is all panic because even though he is not facing Taehyung he can feel shock radiating off of him.  He turns his head and his gaze immediately lands on big, brown eyes that look like they hold a world of hurt.  Jimin gasps and awakens from the fantasy he was playing out in full view of everyone.

His good friend Kai is whispering something to Jungkook.  Kai, who knows about Jimin and Taehyung…Kai, who never knew about Jimin and Jungkook.  Jimin had always guarded his relationship with Jungkook…only ever allowing the members to know.

Because Jimin was always protective of Jungkook…he guarded the golden maknae like he was the most precious thing in existence…because he was.   Jungkook was untainted by their celebrity…he was trusting, loving, and full of hope.  Jungkook had never been betrayed or abused by someone who was supposed to love him…until now.


Read more….

by namjoon4president

Namjoon reached out and his fingers lightly grazed Seokjin’s as he took the cup, causing him to inhale sharply and a little too noticeably, much to Seokjin’s chagrin. But he couldn’t help his reaction, for when their skin met Seokjin felt something akin to an electric current buzz through his finger tips. Not a painful one, but rather shocking at the unexpected sensation. Namjoon’s eyes widened at that and gazed more purposefully into Seokjin’s with slight surprise, leaning forward almost imperceptibly, like he was searching for something. The whole encounter lasted maybe two seconds, but it felt like an eternity. Seokjin couldn’t break away from the eye contact this time despite his embarrassment and was grateful when Namjoon straightened up slightly, blinking once, his face settling back into his polite expression from before as if that moment hadn’t happened.
